## Finally!

Dart gives us a third block: `finally {}`.
It attaches to the bottom of the try/catch stack. Whether the code succeeded perfectly, OR crashed and burned into the catch block... the `finally` block ALWAYS executes!

```dart
try {
  print('Opening File');
  // ... bad read code crashes here ...
} catch (e) {
  print('Caught an error!');
} finally {
  print('Closing File... Cleanup complete!');
}
```
